    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against a required level 3 due to single-condition F1717 testing; this gap is accepted because the single condition is the regulatory standard and clinical risk does not warrant additional loading configurations at this submission stage. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established quantitative acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is deemed credible for its intended use in regulatory submission supporting the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
